content: I'm glad you provided those resources. I think it's interesting how emotional intelligence is often seen as a feminine trait, but it's really important for men to develop it too. I've been trying to work on my emotional intelligence, especially after taking that online quiz that made me realize I've been performing masculinity in ways that don't feel authentic to me. Do you think emotional intelligence can help me in my personal relationships, like with my sister who recently came out as bisexual?
